				<p><p>Normally, the integral term of a PID handles something like the incline.  This takes time to build up error, and as you noticed in your application it is taking some time for the PID to decide to output the proper amount of force when you first encounter the incline.</p>

<p>My guess is that the simplest way to fuse the IMU data would be to use it as a replacement for (or augmentation of) the integral term in your calculation.  Rather than accumulate error over time, the IMU could give you a more instantaneous value.  </p>
